---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Welcome" description="Mentu Documentation - The Commitment Ledger">
  <p class="hero-text">
    Welcome to the Mentu documentation. Learn how to use the commitment ledger to make work traceable.
  </p>

  <h2>Quick Links</h2>

  <div class="quick-links">
    <a href="/knowledge-base/getting-started/quickstart/" class="quick-link">
      <h3>Quickstart</h3>
      <p>Get running in 5 minutes</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/knowledge-base/core-concepts/overview/" class="quick-link">
      <h3>Core Concepts</h3>
      <p>Understand the protocol</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/knowledge-base/cli-reference/overview/" class="quick-link">
      <h3>CLI Reference</h3>
      <p>All commands documented</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/knowledge-base/api-reference/overview/" class="quick-link">
      <h3>API Reference</h3>
      <p>HTTP endpoints</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>What is Mentu?</h2>

  <p>
    Mentu is <strong>The Commitment Ledger</strong> - an append-only ledger that tracks commitments and proof.
    Observations become Commitments, Commitments require Evidence, and Closure demands Proof.
  </p>

  <div class="quick-links" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
    <a href="/knowledge-base/architecture/overview/" class="quick-link">
      <h3>Architecture</h3>
      <p>System design & data flow</p>
    </a>

    <a href="/knowledge-base/guides/github-integration/" class="quick-link">
      <h3>Guides</h3>
      <p>Integration tutorials</p>
    </a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
